  id:"fb-003", source_type:"github", source_subtype:"cloudflare/workers-sdk", stakeholder_type:"developer",
  title:"D1 returns SQLITE_BUSY under concurrent writes — no retry logic",
  raw_text:`D1 throws SQLITE_BUSY errors when multiple Worker instances write concurrently to the same table. There's no built-in retry or queue — you have to implement your own backoff. For a serverless database this is a serious design gap.

At >50 concurrent requests we get ~15% error rate on writes. Switched to a Durable Object to serialize writes as a workaround but that adds 30-40ms latency. AWS Aurora Serverless handles this transparently.

This is blocking us from migrating our production app to D1. We're currently on PlanetScale.`,
